From: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Date: Sun, 9 Mar 2025 17:06:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] iio: light: rpr0521: Switch to sparse friendly
 iio_device_claim/release_direct()
Git-commit: e0dc0feb991b07df6b4b80d5fd417a3967b8ebb7
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-15409

These new functions allow sparse to find failures to release
direct mode reducing chances of bugs over the claim_direct_mode()
functions that are deprecated.

Reviewed-by: David Lechner <dlechner@baylibre.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250309170633.1347476-13-jic23@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.com>
---
 drivers/iio/light/rpr0521.c | 6 ++----
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/iio/light/rpr0521.c b/drivers/iio/light/rpr0521.c
index 65c60a1d2f0b..92e7552f3e39 100644
--- a/drivers/iio/light/rpr0521.c
+++ b/drivers/iio/light/rpr0521.c
@@ -743,19 +743,17 @@ static int rpr0521_read_raw(struct iio_dev *indio_dev,
 {
 	struct rpr0521_data *data = iio_priv(indio_dev);
 	int ret;
-	int busy;
 
 	switch (mask) {
 	case IIO_CHAN_INFO_RAW:
 		if (chan->type != IIO_INTENSITY && chan->type != IIO_PROXIMITY)
 			return -EINVAL;
 
-		busy = iio_device_claim_direct_mode(indio_dev);
-		if (busy)
+		if (!iio_device_claim_direct(indio_dev))
 			return -EBUSY;
 
 		ret = rpr0521_read_info_raw(data, chan, val);
-		iio_device_release_direct_mode(indio_dev);
+		iio_device_release_direct(indio_dev);
 		if (ret < 0)
 			return ret;
 
-- 
2.43.0

